# Test Coverage Requirements

Stack: **pytest**, **pytest-cov**, **coverage** (see `backend/requirements-dev.txt`).

## Global threshold

- Minimum **95%** line coverage on `app/` (enforced via `pytest.ini` / `.coveragerc` `fail_under`).
- Omitted from measurement: `app/main.py`, `alembic/*`.

## 100% required layers

These modules **must** reach **100%** line coverage before merging:

| Layer | Path | Rationale |
|-------|------|-----------|
| Services | `app/services/` | Business rules and transaction boundaries |
| Repositories | `app/repositories/` | Data access contracts |

Enforced programmatically in `tests/conftest.py` (`pytest_sessionfinish` hook).

## Other layers

| Layer | Target | Notes |
|-------|--------|-------|
| API routes | Best effort | Thin handlers; cover success and mapped error paths |
| Agents / tools | Best effort | Mock LLM and RAG dependencies |
| Core infra (`database.py`, `qdrant.py`) | Best effort | Often exercised via integration; not in 100% group |
| RAG | High | Prefer full coverage on pure logic (`chunking`, `service`) |

## How to run

```bash
cd backend
pytest                                    # runs with coverage + thresholds
pytest --cov=app --cov-report=term-missing
```

## Adding tests

| Change type | Test location |
|-------------|---------------|
| Service business rule | `tests/unit/services/test_<service>.py` |
| Repository query | `tests/unit/repositories/test_<repo>.py` |
| HTTP endpoint | `tests/api/test_<feature>.py` |
| Agent / tool | `tests/unit/agents/` or `tests/unit/tools/` |

Use in-memory SQLite via `conftest.py` fixtures (`db_session`, `client`). Mock external APIs (OpenAI, Qdrant) — never call real vendors in tests.

## Checklist before merge

1. `pytest` passes with no coverage failures.
2. New/changed code in `app/services/` or `app/repositories/` has tests covering all branches.
3. Error paths and rollback paths are tested for transactional services.
